<h2>Data Table</h2>
<p>The blocks-layer home for the <a href="/intents/collection-operations/">Collection Operations</a> intent's <strong><code>filter</code>, <code>sort</code>, and <code>group</code> stages</strong> — the three pipeline stages the <a href="/blocks/pagination/">Pagination block</a> (the <code>page</code> stage) leaves unrealized. It renders a native <code>&lt;table&gt;</code> whose sortable column headers project the intent's <code>sortDirection</code> onto the WAI-ARIA APG <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/ARIA/Reference/Attributes/aria-sort"><code>aria-sort</code></a> attribute, orders rows through <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Intl/Collator"><code>Intl.Collator</code></a>, narrows them by <code>filterMatch</code>, and partitions them into <code>&lt;tbody&gt;</code> groups with SQL-named aggregate summaries. It <strong>consumes</strong> the intent's vocabulary verbatim — it does not reinvent it.</p>

<p style="font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--color-text-muted);">
  <strong>Terminology:</strong> See <a href="/semantics/">Semantics &amp; Glossary</a> for terms like
  <a href="/semantics/#term-aria-sort">aria-sort</a>,
  <a href="/semantics/#term-sortable-table">sortable table</a>,
  <a href="/semantics/#term-filter-match">filter match</a>, and
  <a href="/semantics/#term-group-summary">group summary</a>.
</p>

