<h3>Architecture</h3>
<p>Data Table is a <strong>Module</strong> that composes the <code>filter</code>, <code>sort</code>, and <code>group</code> stages of Collection Operations; it owns only set selection/ordering and the table projection, delegating the rest to its neighbours:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>DataTableModule</strong>: resolves the row set, runs the configurable stage pipeline (<code>applyPipeline</code>: default <code>filter → sort → group → page</code>), and exposes the normalized groups.</li>
  <li><strong>DataTableBehavior</strong> (<code>sort:header</code>): attaches to the table, renders <code>&lt;th scope="col"&gt;</code> headers, projects the primary sort key onto <code>aria-sort</code>, and emits <code>sortchange</code> / <code>filterchange</code> / <code>groupchange</code>.</li>
  <li><a href="/blocks/pagination/">Pagination</a> owns the <code>page</code> slice + URL/advance; <a href="/intents/windowed-collection/">Windowed Collection</a> owns which rows are realized in the DOM; <a href="/intents/selection/">Selection</a> is an orthogonal co-resident axis. <strong>Compose, never merge.</strong></li>
</ul>

<h3>The three stages</h3>
<p><strong>Sort</strong> — the only stage with internal depth. The active key's direction projects onto <code>aria-sort</code> on its <code>&lt;th&gt;</code>; text comparison runs through <code>Intl.Collator</code> honoring <code>textSensitivity</code>, <code>numericOrdering</code>, <code>caseFirst</code>, and <code>ignorePunctuation</code>; <code>emptyPlacement</code> mirrors SQL <code>NULLS FIRST/LAST</code> and is <em>direction-independent</em>. <code>sortKeys: multiple</code> stacks keys (ties on the first break on the next); <code>single</code> uses only the primary.</p>
<p><strong>Filter</strong> — call-site predicates combined by <code>filterMatch</code>: <code>all</code> = AND, <code>any</code> = OR. The predicates themselves are app data; the intent owns only how they combine.</p>
<p><strong>Group</strong> — rows partition into one <code>&lt;tbody&gt;</code> per group, each led by a summary row whose value is the <code>groupSummary</code> aggregate (<code>count</code> / <code>sum</code> / <code>average</code> / <code>minimum</code> / <code>maximum</code>), named after the SQL aggregate functions.</p>

<h3>Accessibility contract (verified)</h3>
<ul>
  <li>A native <code>&lt;table&gt;</code>; column headers are <code>&lt;th scope="col"&gt;</code>; sortable headers wrap their label in a <code>&lt;button&gt;</code> (APG Sortable Table recipe).</li>
  <li>Exactly one header carries <code>aria-sort</code> ∈ {<code>ascending</code>, <code>descending</code>} when a sort is active, matching the primary key; every other sortable header is <code>aria-sort="none"</code>; non-sortable headers carry no <code>aria-sort</code>.</li>
  <li>Each group's summary row uses <code>scope="rowgroup"</code> so the aggregate is associated with the group's cells.</li>
  <li><strong>Live interactivity (wired):</strong> clicking a sortable header cycles its state <code>none → ascending → descending → none</code> (re-running the pipeline), and every sort/filter/group change is announced through one polite <code>aria-live</code> region as a clause-joined status — e.g. <em>"Sorted by Salary, descending; 3 of 6 shown"</em> — the Data Table analogue of pagination's "page 2 of 10" (<a href="/backlog/059-pagination-focus-announcement/">#059</a>). Exercised live in the <a href="/demos/data-table-demo.html">playground</a> and in CI.</li>
  <li><strong>Open:</strong> <code>role="grid"</code> cell-level keyboard (arrow-key) navigation — a distinct interaction model from the read-only Sortable Table — remains out of scope here; it composes <a href="/intents/focus-delegation/">Focus Delegation</a> and belongs in a <a href="/backlog/123-data-grid-cell-navigation-block/">separate Data Grid block</a>.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Composition &amp; seam decisions</h3>
<p>The <code>sortDirection → aria-sort</code> projection is exposed as a named <code>sort:header</code> behavior seam — plausibly reusable on a non-table sortable header bar — but realized inside this block; extracting a standalone behavior is deferred until a second, non-table consumer exists. Virtualization stays with <a href="/intents/windowed-collection/">Windowed Collection</a> and paging with <a href="/blocks/pagination/">Pagination</a>; this block renders the full filtered/sorted/grouped set and composes those neighbours on the same collection.</p>

<h3>HTML Usage</h3>
<we-code-view><pre><code class="language-html">&lt;!-- Sortable table: the active column projects aria-sort; a button toggles it --&gt;
&lt;table sort:header&gt;
  &lt;thead&gt;
    &lt;tr&gt;
      &lt;th scope="col" aria-sort="ascending"&gt;&lt;button type="button" data-action="sort" data-field="name"&gt;Name&lt;/button&gt;&lt;/th&gt;
      &lt;th scope="col" aria-sort="none"&gt;&lt;button type="button" data-action="sort" data-field="team"&gt;Team&lt;/button&gt;&lt;/th&gt;
      &lt;th scope="col"&gt;Location&lt;/th&gt;&lt;!-- non-sortable: no aria-sort --&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;/thead&gt;
  &lt;tbody data-group="Engineering"&gt;
    &lt;tr class="group-row"&gt;&lt;th scope="rowgroup" colspan="3"&gt;Engineering — count: 2&lt;/th&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
    &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Aaron&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Engineering&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Oslo&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;</code></pre></we-code-view>

<h3>Interface (contracts only)</h3>
<p>Web Everything defines the contract; concrete strategy implementations (an alternate comparator, server-delegated ordering, a virtualization provider) live in <strong>Frontier UI</strong> and register against these seams without changing the contract.</p>
<we-code-view><pre><code class="language-typescript">type SortDirection = 'ascending' | 'descending';            // aria-sort
type Sensitivity   = 'base' | 'accent' | 'case' | 'variant'; // Intl.Collator
type EmptyPlacement = 'first' | 'last';                      // SQL NULLS FIRST/LAST
type FilterMatch   = 'all' | 'any';
type GroupSummary  = 'count' | 'sum' | 'average' | 'minimum' | 'maximum'; // SQL aggregates
type Operation     = 'filter' | 'sort' | 'group' | 'page';

interface SortKey {
  field: string;
  direction: SortDirection;
  // Comparison preferences mirror Intl.Collator option names verbatim
  sensitivity?: Sensitivity;
  numeric?: boolean;            // natural numeric order: img2 before img10
  caseFirst?: 'upper' | 'lower' | 'false';
  ignorePunctuation?: boolean;
  emptyPlacement?: EmptyPlacement;  // default 'last'; direction-independent
}

interface DataTableContract {
  // `format` is display-only (#368): sort/filter/group always run on the raw `field` value, so
  // Intl.Collator order is unaffected. A string is set as textContent (escape-safe); a Node is a
  // rich cell (e.g. a status chip from the status-indicator standard). Currency/dates via Intl.
  columns: { field: string; label: string; sortable?: boolean; format?: (value: Cell, row: Row) => string | Node }[];
  order?: Operation[];          // default ['filter','sort','group','page']
  filter?: { match: FilterMatch; predicates: ((row: Row) => boolean)[] };
  sort?:   { by: SortKey[]; keys: 'single' | 'multiple' };
  group?:  { field: string; summary: GroupSummary; summaryField?: string };
  // Observable events: 'sortchange' | 'filterchange' | 'groupchange'.
}</code></pre></we-code-view>

<h3>Status &amp; scope</h3>
<p><code>status: draft</code> — the contract, the APG/Intl.Collator/SQL-aggregate design, and a fixture-driven
<a href="/demos/data-table-demo.html">conformance demo</a> ship here; concrete strategy implementations
(comparator providers, server-delegated ordering, virtualization) are deferred to Frontier UI. The
<code>page</code> stage is the separate <a href="/blocks/pagination/">Pagination block</a>. Click-to-sort
wiring and live-region announcements on stage changes are now realized (a live playground card + CI);
<code>role="grid"</code> cell navigation stays out of scope for a distinct block.</p>
